CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Consumer Health Information – Termination Date and Mandatory Funding for
3 the State’s Consumer Health Information Hub – Repeal
4 FOR the purpose of repealing the requirement that the Governor include in the annual
5 budget bill a certain appropriation to the State’s Consumer Health Information Hub;
6 requiring the Hub to carry out certain duties to the extent funding is available;
7 repealing the termination date for certain provisions of law related to consumer
8 health information and the State’s Consumer Health Information Hub; and
9 generally relating to consumer health information.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – Health – General
12 Section 20–2203
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – Health – General
17 Section 20–2204
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
